{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n`test_completion_floor_e2e.py::test_non_regression_floor_is_review_only` (`:178-198`) asserts,\nvia `inspect.getsource` over the floor functions, that tokens like `sign_manifest`,\n`transition`, `reopen(` are ABSENT from their source, and that `completion_floor` does not\nappear in `rebar.llm.completion`. A pure change-detector: a rename / helper / indirect call\nevades it, and it exercises no runtime behavior. VALIDATED.\n\nContext on what is testable: the floor's DECISION logic (which findings drop / are preserved /\nresurface on reopen) is ALREADY behaviorally covered by the sibling tests in this file\n(`test_floor_drops_and_preserves_per_gold_labels`, `test_floor_inactive_is_byte_identical`,\n`test_reopen_resurfaces_dropped_finding`). And `_apply_completion_floor_to_verdict` is a PURE\nverdict→verdict transform (no `repo_root`, no store/LLM I/O), so \"it doesn't sign/transition\"\ncannot be shown by a store snapshot or by spying a close-path function it structurally never\ncalls — those tests are vacuous. The genuine, non-vacuous, non-duplicative behavioral content\nthe old test was reaching for is the floor's **observable purity contract**: it only\nre-partitions findings and never emits any signing/attestation side-output.\n\n## What\nReplace the source-token test with a behavioral **purity-contract** test that runs the real\nfloor over the existing gold fixture (a case that drops a finding) and asserts on OBSERVABLE\nstate:\n1. **Findings conserved (no create/lose/rewrite):** the multiset of finding ids across\n   `advisory ∪ dropped` after the floor equals the set before — the floor only moves findings\n   between the two lists (this is the observable analogue of \"never signs/transitions/reopens\";\n   a floor that fabricated or dropped-without-recording a finding would fail it).\n2. **No signing/attestation side-output:** the returned/mutated verdict grows NO\n   `signature` / `attestation` / `attestations` key, and no new attestation KIND — the floor's\n   only additions are the `dropped` list and the `coverage` narrowing annotation. (Assert the\n   set of top-level verdict keys added by the floor ⊆ {`dropped`, and coverage sub-keys}.)\n3. **Inputs not mutated:** the `cmap` argument and each finding's own content dict are unchanged\n   by identity/value — the floor re-partitions list membership only, it does not rewrite the\n   caller's inputs. (Deep-copy the inputs before the call; assert equal after.)\n4. Keep the genuine artifact-contract assertion `attest._MANIFEST_PREFIX == \"plan-review\"`\n   (no NEW attestation kind exists) — a real invariant, not a source grep.\n\nDelete the `inspect.getsource` token-absence assertions (for the floor functions and for\n`rebar.llm.completion`). The confinement-of-the-floor-to-plan-review property is NOT asserted\nbehaviorally, because it is a negative over a pure, structurally-separated function (any such\ntest is vacuous against the current code); it is left to the module structure, and this ticket\nconverts the false-confidence source grep into the real, observable purity assertions above.\n\n## Scope\n- `tests/unit/test_completion_floor_e2e.py` — replace `test_non_regression_floor_is_review_only`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A behavioral test runs the floor over the gold fixture and asserts findings are CONSERVED\n      (the id set across `advisory ∪ dropped` is identical before/after — nothing fabricated or\n      silently lost).\n- [ ] The test asserts the floor adds NO `signature`/`attestation`/`attestations` key to the\n      verdict (its only additions are `dropped` + the coverage narrowing).\n- [ ] The test asserts the floor does not mutate its `cmap` input or the finding content dicts\n      (pure re-partition) — verified against deep copies taken before the call.\n- [ ] No `inspect.getsource` token-absence assertion remains; the\n      `attest._MANIFEST_PREFIX == \"plan-review\"` artifact contract is retained.\n- [ ] `make test` green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783802401315844001,"uuid":"fe4ab5c2-6376-4403-ba1a-7dbda043f7c6"}